### FFmpeg License (LGPLv2.1)

This project uses [FFmpeg](https://ffmpeg.org), which is licensed under the [GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1](https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.1.html) (LGPLv2.1).

When dynamically linking to FFmpeg libraries, the LGPLv2.1 allows you to use the libraries without placing restrictions on your project's code, as long as the following conditions are met:

- Any modifications made to FFmpeg must be released under the LGPLv2.1.
- Users must be able to replace or relink FFmpeg with their own version if they choose.
- You must provide information to allow users to obtain the FFmpeg source code and relink or modify the library.

If you distribute FFmpeg with your project, ensure that you include the necessary LGPLv2.1 notices, as well as instructions on how users can obtain and relink their own version of FFmpeg.

### yt-dlp License (Unlicense)

This project also incorporates [yt-dlp](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp), a popular tool for downloading videos from various platforms. `yt-dlp` is licensed under [The Unlicense](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/blob/master/LICENSE), a very permissive public domain dedication. The key points are:

- You are free to use, modify, and distribute `yt-dlp` without restriction.
- The code is offered as-is, without warranty, to the extent permitted by law.

You can find more information about The Unlicense at [unlicense.org](https://unlicense.org).

### Compliance

To comply with the different licenses in this project:

- **MIT License**: You are free to use, modify, and distribute the project code, as long as the MIT license is included.
- **LGPLv2.1 (FFmpeg)**: If you dynamically link FFmpeg, ensure users can relink or replace FFmpeg. If you modify or statically link FFmpeg, provide access to the source code and allow users to relink.
- **Unlicense (yt-dlp)**: You are free to use, modify, and distribute `yt-dlp` without any restrictions.

